============
 Filecatman 
============

A file categorization management program for command line and scripting use.

Homepage: https://github.com/fcmadmin/filecatman2

Author: Rich T

==========================
Installation Instructions:
==========================

Ensure python3.10+ is installed.

Run from venv (recommended):
	Linux in terminal:
		1. $ python -m venv ./venv
		2. $ source venv/bin/activate
		3. $ pip install .
		4. $ filecatman
	Windows in admin CMD:
		1. $ python -m venv .\venv
		2. $ .\venv\Scripts\activate
		3. $ pip install .
		4. $ filecatman
	Mac in terminal:
		1. $ python -m venv ./venv
		2. $ source venv/bin/activate
		3. $ pip install .
		4. $ filecatman

Or install on OS:
	Linux in terminal (Requires pip and python 3.10+):
		1. $ sudo pip install .
		2. $ filecatman
	Windows in admin CMD (requires python 3.10+):
		1. $ pip install .
		2. (add the installation directory to the Windows PATH)
		3. $ filecatman
	Mac in terminal (requires python 3.10+):
		1. $ sudo python -m pip install .
		2. $ filecatman

Or run from source:
	1. $ pip install -r requirements.txt
	2. $ python maindev.py

===================
Usage Instructions:
===================

To see usage and command instructions: $ filecatman --help


